defaultOur forthcoming policy paper on strategic planning (mid 2014) will address how planning over areas larger than a single local authority could best be undertaken.
default Some key issues such as housing and waste need solutions at subnational level. 
defaultT
defaulthe use o
defaultf larger areas makes the scope for initiatives for investment now to save later easier. 
defaultThis is because savings in one sectoral budget may only be realised by investments in another. Larger areas 
defaultcould be
default more able to absorb the peaks and troughs on spendi
defaultng involved.
